28/06/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- Parliament started debating the government's controversial bill for social security reforms Monday (27 June), amid a fourth week of protests by banking sector employees. 
Economy and Finance Minister Giorgos Alogoskoufis told deputies that the government is committed to implementing planned structural reforms, while seeking a settlement with unions upset over the restructuring of their pensions.
Also Monday, prosecutors announced the launch of an investigation into the alleged involvement of Greeks in the 1995 Srebrenica massacre. 
Justice Minister Anastasios Papaligouras says there are indications Greek nationals might have fought alongside Bosnian Serbs. 
(Kathimerini - 28/06/05; ANA, MPA, Reuters - 27/06/05)
